---
import Layout from '../../Base.astro';
import SimpleHero from '../../components/SimpleHero.astro';
import FeaturedArticles from "../../components/FeaturedArticles.astro";
import ServicesRelatedWork from "../../components/ServicesRelatedWork.astro";
import "../../styles/pages/_services-list.scss";
---

<Layout
	title='Apparel Design | Florida T-Shirt Design Company'
	description={`When your brand has fans but nothing wearable they actually want to keep, apparel becomes wasted spend. We design merch people want to wear and businesses can confidently produce.`}
>
	<SimpleHero tagline='Branding & Design Services' title='Apparel Design' description="When your brand has fans but nothing wearable they actually want to keep, apparel becomes wasted spend. We design merch people want to wear and businesses can confidently produce." lottieFile="apparel-design.json"/>
	<div class='service-body'>
		<div class='wrapper wrapper--narrow'>
			<h2>Where teams get stuck</h2>
			<p>Apparel usually gets treated like an easy add-on: print a shirt, hand out a hat, make a patch. But when the design is generic or disconnected from the brand, the pieces do not get worn, shared, or remembered.</p>
			<p>That turns merchandise into extra inventory instead of a useful brand touchpoint.</p>
			<h2>How we fix it</h2>
			<p>We design apparel around the real use case, the audience, and the production method so the concept holds up on the actual garment, not just on a screen.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Patches</li>
				<li>Hats</li>
				<li>T-Shirts</li>
				<li>Outerwear</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>What moving forward looks like</h2>
			<p>If you need merch for staff, events, retail, or a product drop, we can help define the concept, build the artwork, and prepare production-ready files so you know exactly what should happen next.</p>
			<p><a href='/contact/' class='button button--green'>Talk Through Your Apparel Project</a></p>
		</div>
		<ServicesRelatedWork tag={67} />
	</div>
	<FeaturedArticles />
</Layout>
